The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, December 29, 2003  Calcutta Column
 
	Sale of cakes and pastries reaches an all-time high in  the year-end, with Christmas and New Year celebrations.  But apart from some reputed shops, most confectioners use  harmful colours in the foodstuff. The civic authorities  must check this potential health hazard.  
	Piyal Mukherjee, Lake Town.  
	The owner of a shop at 15, HM Road stacks coal on the footpath,  while an eatery-owner litters the roadside. Waiters of the  eatery block the kerb by setting up benches. Pedestrians  are forced to walk along the carriageway. If this goes unchecked,  pedestrians should not be blamed for jaywalking.  
	Residents of HM Road. 

